    "Each runnable level relies on the dependencies defined at that level and does not depend on those defined at subsequent levels.",
    "For example, plib-runnable indicate that the task requires public third-party libraries, while file-runnable require dependencies defined in the current file (e.g., user-defined classes and functions).",
    "We remove the tasks overlapping with the training dataset of TOOLGEN, resulting in a final dataset containing 176 tasks.2) Baselines: The different variants of TOOLGEN and the baselines are presented in Table I, along with the base models they employ.Vanilla Baselines.",
    "We develop three vanilla baseline approaches by fine-tuning these same base models but performing straightforward code generation without tool integration.",
    "Specifically, the fine-tuning process for the baselines involves using the 249,298 pairs of descriptions and functions from the augmented dataset."
